msContents.summary: Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation, and is a Hindu philosophical treatise containing about forty-five small upaniṣads derived primarily from the Atharvaveda, a work that is largely dedicated to various Hindu and Vedic deities and addresses various household rites and rituals and their interpretation.
